<paragraph id="B80636A2AF79FFB1FEFEFDF3FB6FFCD8" blockId="9.[192,1442,621,885]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">
This species was incorrectly synonymized with 
<taxonomicName id="7FB94D21AF79FFB1FCF2FDF3FB8BFD2B" authority="(Perty, 1830)" baseAuthorityName="Perty" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[780,1114,621,647]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Ellychnia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="moesta">
<emphasis id="8ACDEAB0AF79FFB1FCF2FDF3FC15FD2B" box="[780,964,621,647]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Ellychnia moesta</emphasis>
(Perty, 1830)
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="DC284B53AF79FFB1FB7EFDF3FA87FD24" author="McDermott FA" box="[1152,1366,621,648]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" refId="ref8299" refString="McDermott FA. 1966. Lampyridae. In: Steel WO (ed.). Coleopterorum catalogus supplementa, pars 9. Uitgeverij Dr. W. Junk; Gravenhage, Netherlands. 149 p." type="book" year="1966">McDermott (1966)</bibRefCitation>
. There are clear size (
<taxonomicName id="7FB94D21AF79FFB1FE9EFD0EFE1BFD05" baseAuthorityName="Perty" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[352,458,655,681]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Ellychnia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="moesta">
<emphasis id="8ACDEAB0AF79FFB1FE9EFD0EFEA1FD05" box="[352,368,656,681]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="8ACDEAB0AF79FFB1FE83FD0EFE1BFD05" box="[381,458,656,681]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">moesta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is larger) and pronotal differences (
<taxonomicName id="7FB94D21AF79FFB1FCA0FD0EFC19FD05" baseAuthorityName="Perty" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[862,968,655,681]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Ellychnia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="moesta">
<emphasis id="8ACDEAB0AF79FFB1FCA0FD0EFCBFFD05" box="[862,878,656,681]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="8ACDEAB0AF79FFB1FC85FD0EFC19FD05" box="[891,968,656,681]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">moesta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a dark pronotum, whereas 
<taxonomicName id="7FB94D21AF79FFB1FAD2FD0EFA71FD05" authorityName="Gorham" authorityYear="1884" box="[1324,1440,655,681]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Photinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="moestus">
<emphasis id="8ACDEAB0AF79FFB1FAD2FD0EFAEAFD05" box="[1324,1339,656,681]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="8ACDEAB0AF79FFB1FAB6FD0EFA71FD05" box="[1352,1440,656,681]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">moestus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a mostly red pronotum). 
<taxonomicName id="7FB94D21AF79FFB1FDF1FD2FFD00FD67" authorityName="Gorham" authorityYear="1884" box="[527,721,689,715]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Photinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="moestus">
<emphasis id="8ACDEAB0AF79FFB1FDF1FD2FFD00FD67" box="[527,721,689,715]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Photinus moestus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was subsequently recognized as a valid species by 
<bibRefCitation id="DC284B53AF79FFB1FAE6FD2FFE41FD41" author="Blackwelder RE &amp; Arnett RH" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" refId="ref7984" refString="Blackwelder RE, Arnett RH Jr. 1974. The buprestid beetles, click beetles, fireflies and related groups: Family 60: Lampyridae. In: Blackwelder RE, Arnett RH Jr. (Compiler). Checklist of the beetles of Canada, United States, Mexico, Central America and West Indies (Yellow version). Volume 4. North American Beetle Fauna Project. The Biological Research Institute of America, Inc.; Latham, New York, USA. 15 p." type="book" year="1974">Blackwelder and Arnett (1974)</bibRefCitation>
. Eight specimens were located. The specimen bearing a red “type” label is designated as the 
<typeStatus id="67028800AF79FFB1FF3CFD6AFEFAFCA2" box="[194,299,756,782]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">lectotype</typeStatus>
. The remaining seven specimens are designated as 
<typeStatus id="67028800AF79FFB1FC95FD6AFBC1FCA2" box="[875,1040,756,782]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">paralectotypes</typeStatus>
. Labels for the designated 
<typeStatus id="67028800AF79FFB1FAC2FD6AFA73FCA2" box="[1340,1442,756,782]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">lectotype</typeStatus>
specimen are as follows: “SYN-/TYPE” “Type” “Cubilguitz,/Vera Paz./Champion.” “B.C.A.Col.III.(2)./ 
<taxonomicName id="7FB94D21AF79FFB1FAD5FC88FA49FC9D" authorityName="Laporte" authorityYear="1833" box="[1323,1432,790,817]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Photinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Photinus</taxonomicName>
/ moestus,/Gorham 
<specimenCount id="AEBFFD2BAF79FFB1FE6FFCA7FE77FCFF" box="[401,422,825,851]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
” “ 
<taxonomicName id="7FB94D21AF79FFB1FE3EFCA6FDF4FCFE" authorityName="Laporte" authorityYear="1833" box="[448,549,824,850]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Photinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Photinus</taxonomicName>
/moestus/Gorham.” “NHMUK 013584683”. A red label is added with the following text: “ 
<typeStatus id="67028800AF79FFB1FED4FCC4FE19FCD8" box="[298,456,858,884]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">LECTOTYPE</typeStatus>
/ 
<taxonomicName id="7FB94D21AF79FFB1FE2EFCC4FD23FCD8" authority="Gorham" authorityName="Gorham" authorityYear="1884" box="[464,754,858,884]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Photinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="moestus">
<emphasis id="8ACDEAB0AF79FFB1FE2EFCC4FD5EFCD8" box="[464,655,858,884]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Photinus moestus</emphasis>
Gorham
</taxonomicName>
/Designated by/Martin and Saxton 2020”
</paragraph>
